To open a new tab and direct to google.com upon webpage load, you can use the following code:

<script>
 window.onload = function(){
   window.open('https://www.google.com', '_blank');
 }
</script>

This code listens for the onload event of the webpage, and when it occurs, it opens a new tab using the URL 'https://www.google.com' using the '_blank' attribute.

You can also use the following code to open a new tab and navigate to google.com immediately:

<script>
 window.open('https://www.google.com', '_blank');
</script>

Note: The '_blank' attribute is used to specify that the new tab should be opened in a new window, and not in the current tab.

